Command Component Minecraft Version Updated on Minecraft 1.19.10 Command on Gametest return object containing some command data. [Script] Example code let command = "give @a apple 1 0" let data = player . runCommand ( command ) Every command will return statusCode and statusMessage with additional property every commands Example command property { // S tatus code i n dica t i n g i f t he comma n d work or n o t // 0 : Success // -2147352576 : Error "statusCode" : 0 , // S tatus message is t he message ou t pu t fr om t he comma n d "statusCode" : "<Message/Output from the command>" } Unexecutable command will throw error to the content log containing stringify object of command error property. Use try catch to take the data. This document will show you which command will throw error with [Error] code Ability Note Command /ability accessible with Education Edition toggle enabled Set the target's ability Command: /ability @s mayfly true { "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Ability has been updated" , "value" : true // The value o f t he abili t y } Check all player's ability Command: /ability @s { "details" : "{
 "mayfly": true,
 "mute": false,
 "worldbuilder": false
}
" , "displayString" : "mayfly, mute, worldbuilder" , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "mayfly, mute, worldbuilder" } Check specific player's ability Command: /ability @s mayfly { "details" : "{
 "mayfly": true
}
" , "displayString" : "mayfly = true" , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "mayfly = true" } Alwaysday Similar command: /daylock Command: /alwaysday true { "statusCode" : 0 } Camerashake Add camera shake to the player Command: /camerashake add @s { "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Send a request to the following players for their camera to shake: FrankyRayMS" } Stop camera shake to the player Command: /camerashake add @s { "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Stopping the camera shake for the following players: FrankyRayMS" } Clear Clear player's inventory when there's any item Command: /clear { "itemsRemoved" : [ "64" ], "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Cleared the inventory of FrankyRayMS, removing 64 items" } Clear player's inventory when no item [Error] Command: /clear { "itemsRemoved" : [ "0" ], "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Could not clear the inventory of {player}, no items to remove" } Check item's amount on the player with amount set to 0 Command: /clear @s diamond 0 0 { "playerTest" : [ "FrankyRayMS (64)" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "FrankyRayMS has 64 items that match the criteria" } Clone Successfully clone the area Command: /clone 0 0 0 0 3 0 0 10 0 { "count" : 4 , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "4 block cloned" } No block cloned [Error] { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "No blocks cloned" } Source and destination area are overlap (without filtered force ) [Error] Command: /clone 0 0 0 0 3 0 0 2 0 { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Source and destination can not overlap" } Trying accessing block outside world [Error] Command: /clone 0 -1 0 0 3 0 0 10 0 { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Cannot access blocks outside of the world" } [Personal] Test failed Test again for /clone error: "Too many blocks in the specific area (%1$d > %2$d)" Max blocks (from Minecraft Wiki): 524288 blocks Clearspawnpoint Command: /clearspawnpoin { "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Removed FrankyRayMS's spawn point" } Connect Similar command: /wsserver Gametest Error Gametest didn't support /connect due to lowest permission level (required 2, got 1) and restriction Command: /connect 1 { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Unknown command: wsserver. Please check that the command exists and that you have permission to use it." } Damage Successfully damage the target Command: /damage @s 1 fall { "hurtActors" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Applied damage to FrankyRayMS" } Cannot damage the target [Error] Command: /damage @s 1 fall [Creative] { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Could not apply damage to FrankyRayMS" , "unhurtActors" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ] } Too many damage sources [Error] Command: /damage @s 1 entity_attack entity @e { "statusCode" : -214735276 , "statusMessage" : "There can only be one source entity. Please adjust your selector to limit selection to one entity." } Info Command still run perfectly even there's unhurtable target/entity. The data will returned both hurtActors and unhurtActors . Command: /damage @e 1 fall { "hurtActors" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Applied damage to FrankyRayMS
Could not apply damage to Armor Stand" , "unhurtActors" : [ "Armor Stand" ] } Daylock Similar command: /alwaysday Command: /daylock true { "statusCode" : 0 } Deop Gametest Error Gametest didn't support /deop due to lowest permission level (required 2, got 1) Command: /deop @s { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Unknown command: deop. Please check that the command exists and that you have permission to use it." } Dialogue Successfully open the dialogue Command: /dialogue open @e[type=npc,c=1] @s exp.give { "playerNames" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Dialogue sent to FrankyRayMS." } Difficulty Command: /difficulty p { "difficulty" : "PEACEFUL" , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Set game difficulty to PEACEFUL" } List of "difficulty" value difficulty : - PEACEFUL - EASY - NORMAL - HARD Effect Successfully give effect to target Command: /effect @s saturation { "amplifier" : 0 , "effect" : "saturation" , "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "seconds" : 30 , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Gave Saturation * 0 to FrankyRayMS for 30 seconds" } Clears all effect from target Command: effect @s clear { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Took all effect from FrankyRaymS" } Clears no effect on the target [Error] Command: /effect @s clear { "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Couldn't take any effects from FrankyRayMS as they do not have any" } Enchant Successfully enchant an item Command: /enchant @s sharpness 5 { "playerName" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Enchanting succeeded for FrankyRayMS" } Combining incompatible enchantment [Error] Command: /enchant @s smite 5 { "playerNames" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Smite can't be combined with Sharpness" } Too high enchantment's level [Error] Command: /enchant @s sharpness 10 { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Sharpness does not support level 10" } Add enchantment into incompatible item [Error] Command: /enchant @s fortune 1 { "playerNames" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "The selected enchantment can't be added to the target item: Fortune" } Player didn't hold any item [Error] { "playerNames" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "The target doesn't hold an item: FrankyRayMS" } [Personal] Re-check Recheck returned data from /enchant (Error only) Event No documentation yet! Execute No documentation yet! Fill Successfully fill the area Command: /fill 0 0 0 3 3 3 wool 10 { "blockName" : "Purple Wool" , "fillCount" : 16 , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "16 blocks filled" } Fill 0 blocks [Error] Command: /fill 0 0 0 0 0 0 wool 10 replace wool 0 { "blockName" : "Purple Wool" , "fillCount" : 0 , "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "0 blocks filled" } Place blocks outside of the world [Error] Command: /fill 0 -1 0 0 0 0 wool 10 { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Cannot place blocks outside of the world" } Too many blocks to fill [Error] Command: /fill 0 0 0 50 50 50 wool 10 { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Too many blocks in the specified area (132651 > 32768)" } Fog No documentation yet! Function No documentation yet! Gamemode Successfully change player's gamemode Command: /gamemode spectator { "gamemode" : "%createWorldScreen.gameMode.spectator" , "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Set FrankyRayMS's gamemode to Spectator" } List of "gamemode" value with the right gamemode name gamemode : - Creative : "%createWorldScreen.gameMode.creative" - Survival : "%createWorldScreen.gameMode.survival" - Adventure : "%createWorldScreen.gameMode.adventure" - Default : "%createWorldScreen.gameMode.serverDefault" - Spectator : "%createWorldScreen.gameMode.spectator" Gamerule Update the value of game rule (Boolean) /gamerule commandblockoutput false { "name" : "commandblockoutput" , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Game rule commandblockoutput has been updated to false" , "value" : false } Update the value of game rule (Integer/Number) /gamerule randomtickspeed 4 { "name" : "randomtickspeed" , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Game rule randomtickspeed has been updated to 4" , "value" : 4 } Gametest No documentation yet! Give Successfully give an item to player Command: /give @s apple { "itemAmount" : 1 , "itemName" : "Apple" , "playerName" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Gave Apple * 1 to FrankyRayMS" } Help Similar command: /? Show help (Page) Command: /help 1 { "body" : "<Too long message; Similar to statusMessage, output of command message>" } Show help (Command) Command: /help camerashake { "command" : "camerashake:" , "description" : "%commands.screenshake.description" , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "<Too long message>" } Immutableworld Note Command /immutableworld accessible with Education Edition toggle enabled No documentation yet! Kick Trying to kick operator/admin of the world [Error] Command: /kick FrankyRayMS { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "The host may not be kicked from the game." } [Public] Need test Need testing for successful kicking player from the world Kill Successfully kill the target Command: /kill @a { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Killed Cow, Chicken, Egg, Skeleton, Skeleton, Chicken, Cow" , "targetname" : [ "Cow" , "Chicken" , "Egg" , "Skeleton" , "Skeleton" , "Chicken" , "Cow" ] } Cannot kill the target/no unkillable target [Error] Command: /kill @s { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "No targets matched selector" } List { "currentPlayerCount" : 1 , "maxPlayerCount" : 8 , "players" : "FrankyRayMS" , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "There are 1/8 players online:
FrankyRayMS" } Locate Locating structure Command: /locate ancientcity || /locate structure ancientcity { "destination" : { "x" : 1352 , "y" : 64 , "z" : -1848 }, "feature" : "%feature.ancientcity" , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "The nearest Ancient City is at block 1352, (y?), -1848 (2304 blocks away)" } Locating biome Command: /locate biome plains { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "The nearest plains is at block -101, 63, -210 (243 blocks away)" } [Personal/Public] Need Test Need testing for check unreachable structure/biome location "No valid structure found within a reasonable distance" Loot Gametest Error Gametest cannot run /loot for no reason. Command: /loot give @s loot custom_loot_test { "statusCode" : -2147352576 } Me Command: /me Hello! { "statusCode" : 0 } Mobevent No documentation yet! Msg Similar command: /tell and /w Full documentation on /tell Music No documentation yet! OP Gametest Error Gametest didn't support /op due to lowest permission level (required 2, got 1) Command: /op @s { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Unknown command: op. Please check that the command exists and that you have permission to use it." } Particle No documentation yet! Playanimation No documentation yet! Playsound No documentation yet! Reload Gametest Error Gametest didn't support /reload due to lowest permission level (required 2, got 1) Command: /reload @s { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Unknown command: reload. Please check that the command exists and that you have permission to use it." } Replaceitem No documentation yet! Ride No documentation yet! Say Command: /say Hello! { "message" : "Hello!" , "statusCode" : 0 } Schedule No documentation yet! Scoreboard No documentation yet! Setblock Successfully set block Command: /setblock 0 0 0 stone { "position" : { "x" : 0 , "y" : 0 , "z" : 0 }, "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Block placed" } Setmaxplayers Gametest Error Gametest didn't support /setmaxplayers due to lowest permission level (required 3, got 1) Command: /setmaxplayers @s { "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Unknown command: setmaxplayers. Please check that the command exists and that you have permission to use it." } Setworldspawn { "spawnPoint" : { "x" : -5 , "y" : 58 , "z" : 15 }, "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Set the world spawn point to (-5, 58, 15)" } Spawnpoint Command: /spawnpoint @s { "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "spawnPos" : { "x" : -5 , "y" : 58 , "z" : 15 }, "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Set FrankyRayMS's spawn point to (-5, 58, 15)" } Spreadplayers Command: /spreadplayers -5 15 1 10 @a { "count" : 1 , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Successfully spread 1 players around -5.00,15.00" , "victims" : "FrankyRayMS" , "x" : -5 , "z" : 15 } Stopsound No documentation yet! Structure No documentation yet! Summon Successfully spawn entity Command: /summon shicken { "entityType" : "minecraft:chicken" , "spawnPos" : { "x" : -12.5 , "y" : 70 , "z" : 16.5 }, "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Object successfully summoned" , "uID" : "-12884901746" , "wasSpawned" : true } Tag Successfully add tag Command: /tag @s add Test { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Added tag 'Test' to FrankyRayMS" } Successfully remove tag Command: /tag @s remove Test { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Removed tag 'Test' from FrankyRayMS" } Show player's tags list Command: /tag @s list { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "FrankyRayMS has 1 tags: §aTest§r" } Teleport Similar command: /tp Successfully teleport to other location Command: /teleport 0 4 0 { "destination" : { "x" : 0.5 , "y" : 4 , "z" : 0.5 }, "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Teleported FrankyRayMS to 0.50, 4.00, 0.50" , "victim" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ] } Tell Similar command: /msg and /w Send a message Command: /tell @a Hello! { "message" : "Hello!" , "recipient" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "You whisper to FrankyRayMS: Hello!" } Tellraw Command: /tellraw @a {"rawtext": [{"text": "Hello!"}]} { "recipient" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 } Testfor { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Found FrankyRayMS" , "victim" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ] } Testforblock Success to test Command: /testforblock ~ ~ ~ air { "matches" : true , "position" : { "x" : -13 , "y" : 76 , "z" : 16 }, "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Successfully found the block at -13,76,16." } Fail to test [Error] Command: /testforblock ~ ~ ~ leaves { "matches" : false , "position" : { "x" : -13 , "y" : 76 , "z" : 16 }, "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "The block at -13,76,16 is Air (expected: Spruce Leaves)." } Testforblocks Success to test Command: /testforblocks ~-2 ~-2 ~-2 ~2 ~2 ~2 ~ ~ ~ { "compareCount" : 125 , "matches" : true , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "125 blocks compared" } Fail to test [Error] Command: /testforblocks ~-2 ~-2 ~-2 ~2 ~2 ~2 ~ ~-5 ~ { "matches" : false , "statusCode" : -2147352576 , "statusMessage" : "Source and destination are not identical" } Time Set the time Command: /time set sunset { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Set the time to 36000" , "time: 36000" } Time query Day Daytime Gametime Command: /time query day { "body" : "Day is 1" , "data" : 1 , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Day is 1" } Command: /time query daytime { "body" : "Daytime is 12000" , "data" : 12000 , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Daytime is 12000" } Command: /time query gametime { "body" : "Gametime is 58616" , "data" : 58616 , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Gametime is 58616" } Title Command: /title @a title Hello! { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Title command successfully executed" } Titleraw Command: titleraw @a title {"rawtext": [{"text": "Hello!"}]} { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Titleraw command successfully executed" } Toggledownfall { "rainLevel" : 100 , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Toggled downfall" } TP Similar command: /teleport Volumearea No documentation yet! W Similar command: /msg and /tell Full documentation on /tell WB Similar command: /worldbuilder Weather Change the weather Command: /weather clear { "statusCode" : 0 , "statuseMessage" : "Changing to clear weather" } Weather query Command: /weather query { "data" : 0 , "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Weather state is: clear" } List of "data" value and its weather state data : 0 : clear 1 : rain 2 : thunder XP Successfully add/remove XP level Command: /xp -10L @s { "amount" : -10 , "level" : 3 , "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Taken 10 levels from FrankyRayMS" } Successfully add XP point Command: /xp 10 @s { "amount" : 10 , "level" : 3 , "player" : [ "FrankyRayMS" ], "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Gave 10 experience to FrankyRayMS" } Trying to give negative XP point [Error] Command: /xp -10 @s { "statusCode" : 0 , "statusMessage" : "Cannot give player negative experience points" }

